A vintage 1950s advertising style illustration depicting a frustrated housewife standing alone in her living room, arms crossed, staring at a tangled mess of cables and a disconnected modem on a side table. Through the window, a service van drives away into the distance, leaving a trail of dust. The room features warm amber and teal tones typical of mid-century decor, with a rotary telephone sitting uselessly nearby. The woman's expression conveys exasperation and abandonment. Soft halftone dot texture overlays the entire scene, giving it an authentic retro magazine advertisement quality.
